    <p>The Moving Archer Forward initiative continues to gain momentum with recent community meetings discussing pedestrian safety improvements and bike lane proposals along Archer Avenue. The Chicago Department of Planning and Development (DPD) has extended its community input deadline, signaling strong institutional commitment. Alongside, the Greater Chicago Food Depository broke ground on its new facility, bringing both jobs and infrastructure investment to the Southwest Side corridor. These developments point to a sustained wave of reinvestment in the 60632 industrial belt, with the Crawford Power Plant redevelopment and Midway Airport expansion adding to the momentum.</p>
